==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fire fighter
<hw>fire" fight`er</hw></mhw>
<pr>(f⟦imac⟧r"f⟦imac⟧`t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person whose
occupation it is to go to the scene of an unwanted fire and extinguish
it; a member of a fire company; a <stype>fireman{1}</stype> or a woman
who fights fires.</def> <note>Some towns have few or no professional
firefighters, and fire suppression is conducted mostly by groups of
volunteers, called <stype>volunteer firefighters</stype>. The term
fireman{1} was at one time synonymous with firefighter, until women
began to engage in the same occupation.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firefish</ent>⟦br⟧
